<div class="accordion-item">
    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="bonsaiBidHeading">
        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#bonsaiBidCollapse" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="bonsaiBidCollapse">
            Bonsai Bid
        </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="bonsaiBidCollapse" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="bonsaiBidHeading" data-bs-parent="#workAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
            <!-- Logos at the top, full width -->
            <div class="tech-logos d-flex justify-content-center flex-wrap mb-3">
                @foreach (var logo in TechLogos)
                {
                    <img src="@logo" alt="Technology logo" class="tech-logo me-3 mb-3" />
                }
            </div>
            <!-- Side-by-side description and image containers -->
            <div class="d-flex align-items-start">
                <div class="project-description flex-grow-1 me-3">
                    <ul>
                        <li>Developing a scalable auction platform using Ruby on Rails, integrated with Redis for caching and Sidekiq for background job processing.</li>
                        <li>Implementing dynamic form logic using JavaScript and Stimulus, enabling real-time updates and intuitive user interactions based on input, enhancing the overall user experience.</li>
                        <li>Gaining deep expertise in full-stack development and architecture, continuous deployment with GitHub Actions, and optimizing performance using Skylight.</li>
                        <li>Delivering a high-performance, user-friendly platform while maintaining 95%+ test coverage, facilitating efficient online auctions and supporting business growth.</li>
                        <li>Spearheaded the overall system architecture and design, ensuring scalability, maintainability, and a clean codebase, while making key decisions on database structure, API design, and frontend-backend interaction.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="project-image ms-3 flex-shrink-0">
                    <!-- Placeholder for future project image -->

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
